SoftImpute imputation.

Source: R/imputing.R
impute_softimpute.Rd

A function to replace NA in the data frame by softImpute::softImpute().

Usage

impute_softimpute(missdf, ...)

Arguments

missdf

a data frame with missing values to be imputed containing features in columns and samples in rows.

...

other parameters of softImpute::softImpute() besides x.

Value

A data.frame with imputed values by softImpute::softImpute().

References

Mazumder TH, Rahul (2021). “softImpute: Matrix Completion via Iterative Soft-Thresholded SVD.”

See also

softImpute::softImpute()

Examples

data(sim_miss)
impute_softimpute(sim_miss)
